The paper describes a tool for handling scientific bibliographic information, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category, as Scholia is a tool for managing scholarly profiles and publications. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases) are also likely categories, as Scholia queries the SPARQL-based Wikidata Query Service to collect data. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CY (Computers and Society) are less likely but still possible categories, as Scholia can display co-author networks and citation graphs, and can be used to study research topics.
